msContents.summary: A commentary on Mukhtaṣar fī al-fiqh ʻalá madhhab al-Shāfiʻī (also called al-Taqrīb) by Abū Shujāʻ al-Iṣfahānī, a work on the application of Shāfiʻī jurisprudence.

msItem.title: Fatḥ al-qarīb al-mujīb fī sharḥ alfāẓ al-Taqrīb.
فتح القريب المجيب في شرح الفاظ التقريب

author.persName: Ghazzī, Muḥammad ibn Qāsim, 1454 or 1455-1512 or 1513

respStmt.persName: Ibn al-Habrah, Saʻd ibn Surūd, active 1675

msItem.title: Fatḥ al-qarīb al-mujīb fī sharḥ alfāẓ al-Taqrīb.

supportDesc.extent: 121 leaves : 195 x 135 (140 x 135) mm, bound to 195 x 145 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Rubrications in red including overlining and sets of dots to mark text divisions.

binding.p: Bound in reddish brown leather over pasteboard with flap; blind stamped central mandorla with four radial lines and double frame.

origin.p: Copied completed 9 Dhū al-Hijjah 1086 AH / February 1676 CE by Saʻd ibn Surūd al-shahīr bi-Ibn al-Habrah (f. 126v).
